      "message": "Patch Set 5 summary:\n\nIn-place extension of Item.Dimm instead of introducing a separate\nItem.Memory. PS5 reworks the patch in that direction; Item.Dimm is\nupdated rather than deprecated, and Item.Memory is no longer added.\n\nChanges:\n\n- Generalize DIMM-specific property descriptions (interface\n  description, MemorySizeInKB, MemoryDeviceLocator).\n\n- Add defaults for properties that do not apply to embedded memory\n  (CASLatencies, MemoryAttributes), with a clarifying note in the\n  description that 0 means \"not applicable\".\n\n- Add an Embedded value to the FormFactor enum, since the existing\n  values are either DIMM-specific or describe a single die only.\n\nExisting Item.Dimm producers and consumers are unaffected.\n\nReviews and feedback are appreciated.Thanks.",
